  "body": "The current stratum port implementation works well with stratum1 and ethproxy methods. However, when this port is opened to the world, we see users point at this port and perform HTTP requests.\r\n1. We should simply ignore HTTP traffic that doesn't fit the stratum pattern. It is not interesting.\r\n2. Because miners out there get misconfigured and folks may only have ability to use with getWork/submitWork, we should port over from the HTTP JSON-RPC service the 2 methods eth_getWork and eth_submitWork. These methods can then be safely exposed without exposing the JSON-RPC service.",
